   478	_TAG_INFER_SYSTEM = (
   479	    "You translate a user's plain-language goal into CLI capability tags. "
   480	    "Return ONLY compact JSON: {\"goal_inputs\":[...],\"goal_outputs\":[...],\"side_effects\":[...]}. "
   481	    "Tags use the registry's <category>:<subtype> vocabulary (e.g. file:pdf, text:doc, "
   482	    "file:png) — never plain words or snake_case compounds. "
   483	    "goal_inputs = capability tags the user already has (e.g. file:svg). "
   484	    "goal_outputs = capability tags they want produced (e.g. file:png). "
   485	    "For a QUERY goal that asks a question rather than requesting a file (e.g. "
   486	    "'check git status', 'count lines in a file', 'does this file exist') there is "
   487	    "no output artifact — the goal produces an answer, not a file. Use 'text' or "
   488	    "'json' as goal_outputs for that answer's format; goal_outputs must never be "
   489	    "empty. "
   490	    "For an ACTION goal whose point is a side effect rather than a produced file "
   491	    "(e.g. 'send an email', 'post a webhook', 'write X to a file') there is likewise "
   492	    "no output artifact — the command returns a confirmation, not a file. Use 'text' "
   493	    "as goal_outputs for that confirmation, and put the action in side_effects. "
   494	    "goal_outputs must never be empty, even for pure side-effect goals. "
   495	    "side_effects = side-effect classes the goal explicitly asks for (e.g. email, file_write). "
   496	    "No prose, no code fences."
