codex
The compound-goal start gate in §2.6 is correctly present as `not goal_out`. It matches the current start-selection behavior at `search.py:97-100` and prevents action terminals becoming compound-goal starts.

The §2.7 authorization fix is also present and sound: `_hop_excluded` remains unchanged, the caller’s allow-set is not widened, and the final-position wrapper only exempts an exact matched slug. This creates no mid-chain class-wide leak.

Terminal-edge synthesis is traversable: producer `P` fails the compound terminal predicate, falls through to synthesized adjacency, and enqueues `P→T`; at `T`, the earlier producer satisfies the artifact requirement and `T` satisfies the action requirement.

No additional production `goal_outputs[0]` consumer or separate `plan_cli_chain` schema was found beyond §3’s listed sites. Registry-first deployment is backward-compatible provided `goal_actions` is optional and empty-action behavior remains unchanged. AC-02 through AC-05 are testable as written.

Two implementation-breaking holes remain:

1. §2.2 — The map’s values are pairwise disjoint, and live `email→{send}` uniquely finds `send_mail`, whose row is `intent_tags='notify,send'`. But that same row also matches `notify→{notify}`. Therefore the claimed implication “disjoint map values means no terminal matches two verbs” is false, the stated live validation would fail with `send_mail → {email, notify}`, and a `notify` goal can route to `send_mail`. The third-pass ambiguity hole is not closed.

2. §2.8 / §3 — The claimed reuse of the existing retry loop does not exist on the planner-error path. `_infer_capability_tags` performs its only retry at adapter lines 545-566, before `plan_cli_chain` is called and only for rejected input/output port tags. The planner is then called once at lines 899-905. Moreover, `_unwrap_mcp_json` converts a structured error object into a one-element list, after which `_select_chain` discards its details and raises a generic “no healthy chain” error. The spec must explicitly add planner-error decoding and reinference orchestration—or define a reusable inference retry interface—so the rejected verb and known verbs actually reach the model.

NOT-PLAN-READY
